cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel classification method for multi-task data streams that considers both external correlations between multiple data streams and internal relationships within individual data streams. This involves machine learning techniques such as support vector machines (SVM) and double-coupling learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves image classification tasks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of SVM and other machine learning techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
